      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Female sayona vampire",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role (E7, social encounter):</strong> Scarwall's <strong>war commander</strong> — external troop movements, distinct from the hunt and watch commanders — and the only one outside the walls during Mandraivus's raid… because she was already a blood-drinking <strong>sayona</strong> posing as a living woman. An orc priest's <em>command undead</em> pressed her into the vanguard that retook the castle; the rising curse freed her from orc control and she simply never left. Melancholic, fatalistic, amused by the PCs' zeal (she does not expect them to beat Mithrodar — but the attempt entertains). <strong>Blood for secrets:</strong> she answers questions about Kazavon's last days, Mandraivus's doom, and the castle's history — price: a willing PC lets her drink for at least 1 round (she asks for 4; negotiable). Truthfulness is the GM's choice — use her to reorient a lost party. She feels no urge whatever to defend the castle. <strong>Left alive, she follows:</strong> invisible and gaseous she stalks the party, and once a PC is alone she Dominates him back to E7 to feed — kept alive, and helpless.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
