    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
      "name": "Absorb Blood",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The sayona is adjacent to a bleeding creature</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The sayona absorbs the creature's blood. The creature must attempt a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:35] save. If a creature is targeted with this ability in consecutive rounds, the save DC decreases by 2 each round after the first.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 1} or increases its drained condition by 1 and the sayona regains its level in HP, regaining excess HP as temporary hit points. Absorbing blood from a creature that's already drained doesn't restore any HP to the sayona, but it increases the creature's drained condition value by 1. A sayona can also absorb blood that's been emptied into a vessel for sustenance, but it gains no HP from doing so. The target creature's drained condition value decreases by 1 per week. A blood transfusion, which requires a successful @Check[type:medicine|dc:18] check and sufficient blood or a blood donor, reduces the drained value by 1 after 10 minutes.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 2}.</p>"
        },
